      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The key view loop is actually recalculated the next time someone requests the next or previous key view of the window. The recalculated loop is based on the geometric order of the views in the window."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If you do not want to maintain the key view loop of your window manually, you can use this method to do it for you. When it is first loaded, "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSWindow"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " calls this method automatically if your window does not have a key view loop already established. If you add or remove views later, you can call this method manually to update the windowâ€™s key view loop. You can also set the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nswindow/1419214-autorecalculateskeyviewloop"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to have the window recalculate the loop automatically."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
